Material Information for Capital Markets/Trading Decisions:
- Exploration Results:
- Confirmed Ionic Adsorption Clay (IAC) characteristics at Capão Bonito project, with strong rare earth oxide (REO) recoveries (>50% MREO) via ammonium sulphate leach (AMSUL) testing.
- High-grade intercepts (near-surface):
- 10m @ 66% MREO extraction (CBAD-0005)
- 14m @ 55% MREO (CPO-TD0013)
- 10m @ 89% MREO (CPO-TD0039, pending top 4m results)
- 7m @ 77% MREO (CPO-TD0040).
- Strategic significance: IAC deposits are rare outside China, offering low-cost, environmentally benign processing critical for EV/renewable energy supply chains.

  • Next Steps:
  • Follow-up drilling (late July) to test high-recovery zones.
  • Infill drilling (400m spacing) to confirm mineralization continuity.

  • Metallurgical optimization and mineralogical analysis (19 priority samples).

  • Strategic Impact: Results position Capão Bonito as a high-potential REE discovery, potentially enhancing PVW’s valuation as a clean energy materials player.

Summary of ASX Announcement – Delorean Corporation Ltd (25th June 2025)

Material Regulatory Reforms Impacting Valuation:
- NGER Scheme Changes (effective 1 July 2025):
- Biomethane and hydrogen formally recognised as fuel types, enabling RGGO certificates for Scope 1 emissions reduction.
- Companies using RGGO-certified biomethane can report lower emissions starting 2025–26 (first reports due 31 Oct 2026).

  • AS 4564:2025 (effective 12 June 2025):
  • Biomethane now classified as "natural gas equivalent" with relaxed oxygen (1% mol vs. 0.2%) and tailored contaminant thresholds, reducing upgrade costs.

Strategic Implications for Delorean:
- SA1 Bioenergy Project (Adelaide): GreenPower-registered; RGGO certificate issuance imminent upon biomethane delivery.
- Regulatory clarity reduces project risk, accelerates commercialization, and enhances revenue from biomethane and RGGOs.

No capital raising, financial data, or trading halt requested.

Material Information Summary (Summit Minerals Ltd – ASX:SUM – 25 June 2025)

Key Highlights

  • Metallurgical Test Results: Positive initial results from Equador Project pegmatites confirm high-grade tantalum (Ta) and niobium (Nb) concentrates achievable via simple density separation.
  • Ta Concentrates: Up to 5.3% (specific size fraction); 45x upgrade factor.
  • Nb Concentrates: Up to 2.8% (specific size fraction); 35x upgrade factor.

  • Recoveries: 77–93% for Ta, 52–87% for Nb via Heavy Liquid Separation (HLS); gravity table recoveries up to 97% (Ta) and 92% (Nb).

  • Next Steps:

  • Additional bulk sampling/mineralogical studies planned to optimize crush size and separation methods.

  • Soil sampling results pending for target refinement ahead of drilling.

  • Project Implications: Validates technical viability of simple beneficiation methods for potential operations at Equador.

Trading Implications
